verses.verse: Make a joyful <S%H7321>noise<s%> unto <S%H430>God<s%>, all you <S%H776>lands<s%>:
Sing <S%H2167>forth<s%> the <S%H3519>honor<s%> of his <S%H8034>name<s%>: <S%H7760>make<s%> his <S%H8416>praise<s%> <S%H3519>glorious<s%>.

<S%H559>Say<s%> unto <S%H430>God<s%>, How <S%H3372>terrible<s%> are you in your <S%H4639>works<s%>! through the <S%H7230>greatness<s%> of your <S%H5797>power<s%> shall your <S%H341>enemies<s%> submit themselves unto <S%H3584>you<s%>.
All the <S%H776>earth<s%> shall <S%H7812>worship<s%> <S%H2167>you<s%>, and shall sing unto <S%H2167>you<s%>; they shall sing to your <S%H8034>name<s%>. <S%H5542>Selah<s%>.
<S%H3212>Come<s%> and <S%H7200>see<s%> the <S%H4659>works<s%> of <S%H430>God<s%>: he is <S%H3372>terrible<s%> in his <S%H5949>doing<s%> toward the <S%H1121>sons<s%> of <S%H120>men<s%>.
He <S%H2015>turned<s%> the <S%H3220>sea<s%> into <S%H3004>dry<s%> <S%H5674>land<s%>: they went through the <S%H5104>flood<s%> on <S%H7272>foot<s%>: there did we rejoice in <S%H8055>him<s%>.

He <S%H4910>rules<s%> by his <S%H1369>power<s%> for <S%H5769>ever<s%>; his <S%H5869>eyes<s%> <S%H6822>behold<s%> the <S%H1471>nations<s%>: let not the <S%H5637>rebellious<s%> <S%H7311>exalt<s%> <S%H5542>themselves<s%>. Selah.
O <S%H1288>bless<s%> our <S%H430>God<s%>, you <S%H5971>people<s%>, and make the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of his <S%H8416>praise<s%> to be <S%H8085>heard<s%>:
Which <S%H7760>holds<s%> our <S%H5315>soul<s%> in <S%H2416>life<s%>, and <S%H5414>allowed<s%> not our <S%H7272>feet<s%> to be <S%H4132>moved<s%>.
For <S%H430>you<s%>, O God, have <S%H974>proved<s%> <S%H6884>us<s%>: you have tried <S%H3701>us<s%>, as silver is <S%H6884>tried<s%>.
You <S%H935>brought<s%> us into the <S%H4686>net<s%>; you <S%H7760>laid<s%> <S%H4157>affliction<s%> upon our <S%H4975>body<s%>.

You have caused <S%H582>men<s%> to <S%H7392>ride<s%> over our <S%H7218>heads<s%>; we <S%H935>went<s%> through <S%H784>fire<s%> and through <S%H4325>water<s%>: but you brought us <S%H3318>out<s%> into a wealthy <S%H7310>place<s%>.
I will <S%H935>go<s%> into your <S%H1004>house<s%> with burnt <S%H5930>offerings<s%>: I will <S%H7999>pay<s%> you my <S%H5088>vows<s%>,
Which my <S%H8193>lips<s%> have <S%H6475>uttered<s%>, and my <S%H6310>mouth<s%> has <S%H1696>spoken<s%>, when I was in <S%H6862>trouble<s%>.

I will <S%H5927>offer<s%> unto you burnt <S%H5930>sacrifices<s%> of <S%H4220>fatlings<s%>, with the <S%H7004>incense<s%> of <S%H352>rams<s%>; I will <S%H6213>offer<s%> <S%H1241>bullocks<s%> with <S%H6260>goats<s%>. <S%H5542>Selah<s%>.
<S%H3212>Come<s%> and <S%H8085>hear<s%>, all you that <S%H3373>fear<s%> <S%H430>God<s%>, and I will <S%H5608>declare<s%> what he has <S%H6213>done<s%> for my <S%H5315>soul<s%>.
I <S%H7121>cried<s%> unto him with my <S%H6310>mouth<s%>, and he was <S%H7311>extolled<s%> <S%H8478>with<s%> my <S%H3956>tongue<s%>.
If I <S%H7200>regard<s%> <S%H205>iniquity<s%> in my <S%H3820>heart<s%>, the <S%H136>Lord<s%> will not hear <S%H8085>me<s%>:
But <S%H403>truly<s%> <S%H430>God<s%> has <S%H8085>heard<s%> <S%H7181>me<s%>; he has attended to the <S%H6963>voice<s%> of my <S%H8605>prayer<s%>.
<S%H1288>Blessed<s%> be <S%H430>God<s%>, which has not turned <S%H5493>away<s%> my <S%H8605>prayer<s%>, nor his mercy from <S%H2617>me<s%>.
